<Vertical id="LLMFeedbackDemo" title="LLMFeedback Block Demo">

  <Markdown id="intro">
## LLMFeedback Display Examples

LLMFeedback displays AI-generated responses with a robot icon and loading states.

**Pattern**: LLMFeedback receives responses from LLMAction when triggered via ActionButton.
  </Markdown>

  <!-- Basic usage -->
  <Vertical id="basic_example">
    <Markdown id="q1">
### Basic Feedback Display

Enter a question for the AI to answer:
    </Markdown>
    <TextArea id="user_question" placeholder="Ask a question..." rows="3" />
    <LLMFeedback id="ai_answer" />

    <ActionButton id="ask_btn" label="Ask AI">
      <LLMAction id="ask_action" target="ai_answer">
        Answer this question concisely:
        <Ref id="question_ref" target="user_question" />
      </LLMAction>
    </ActionButton>
  </Vertical>

  <Markdown id="states_explanation">
### LLMFeedback States

The component shows:
- **Nothing** when no request has been made
- **Spinner** while waiting for the LLM response
- **Text** when feedback is received
- **Error message** if something goes wrong
  </Markdown>

  <!-- Multiple feedback displays -->
  <Vertical id="multi_example">
    <Markdown id="q2">
### Multiple Feedback Components

You can have multiple LLMFeedback components, each receiving responses from different LLMActions:
    </Markdown>
    <TextArea id="code_sample" placeholder="Paste code here..." rows="4" />

    <Markdown id="style_label">**Style Review:**</Markdown>
    <LLMFeedback id="style_feedback" />

    <Markdown id="logic_label">**Logic Review:**</Markdown>
    <LLMFeedback id="logic_feedback" />

    <ActionButton id="review_btn" label="Review Code">
      <LLMAction id="style_action" target="style_feedback">
        Review this code for style: <Ref id="style_ref" target="code_sample" />
      </LLMAction>
      <LLMAction id="logic_action" target="logic_feedback">
        Review this code for logic errors: <Ref id="logic_ref" target="code_sample" />
      </LLMAction>
    </ActionButton>
  </Vertical>

  <Markdown id="connection_note">
### Connecting LLMFeedback to LLMAction

The connection is made through matching IDs:
1. LLMFeedback has an `id` (e.g., `id="feedback"`)
2. LLMAction has a `target` pointing to that ID (e.g., `target="feedback"`)
3. LLMAction is nested inside ActionButton for triggering
  </Markdown>

</Vertical>
